# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# FRONTEND ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# Copy this file to .env.production and fill in your values
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Backend API URL
# Development:
# REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:5000

# Production (Render):
REACT_APP_API_URL=https://skill-swap-backend-1bz4.onrender.com
DISABLE_ESLINT_PLUGIN=true

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# NOTES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# - Replace "your-backend-url" with your actual Render backend URL
# - This URL must be the same as your backend's public URL
# - For development, use http://localhost:5000
# - For production, use https://your-service.onrender.com

# - Environment variables starting with REACT_APP_ are available in browser
# - They should NOT contain sensitive information (they are visible in frontend code)

# - Keep .env.production out of git (it's in .gitignore)
# - For Vercel deployment, set these variables in Vercel dashboard instead
